` Additional info `
GitHub Flow Rules:
  #1 - anything in the master branch is deployable
  #2 - create descriptive branches off of master (you can prefix branch names with @hotfix/, @feature/, @post/ )
  #3 - push to named branches constantly
  #4 - open a pull request at any time
  #5 - merge only after pull request review
  #6 - deploy immediately after review


Commit message:



Code StyleGuide / Rules:
  @high - For react styles use modules
  @high - Use Conventional Commits (`https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/`)

Technics (ideas) to use :
  ☐ CI/CD ??? (`https://rollout.io/blog/continuous-integration-continuous-delivery-continuous-deployment/`) (`https://github.com/features/actions`)
    ☐ Make sure Travis CI turns green (or CI environment (Jenkins)) ?
  ☐ Autotest for master branch (bunch of unit tests, or regression tests, accessibility tests) ???
    ☐ Consider to code coverage tests over 90%, to successfull merge to `master` branch
    ☐ Autocheck modules vulnerabilites (audit, dependabot???) to successfull merge to `master` branch
  ☐ Consider to use 'semantic-release' - `https://github.com/semantic-release/semantic-release`
  ☐ Consider to use 'size-limit' - `https://github.com/ai/size-limit`
  ☐ Protect master branch to direct commit push


